ANTHRAX - BULGARIA (02): (VARNA), BOVINE, HUMAN
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: 20 Jul 2015
Source: Focus Information Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2015/07/20/378418/22-individuals-test-negative-for-anthrax-over-possible-outbreak-in-bulgarias-varna-district-medic.html


It was announced on Sat [18 Jul 2015] that a 53-year-old man from the village of Mlada Gvardiya, municipality of Vetrino, district of Varna, and his cow were infected with anthrax. Both the man and the animal died recently. [The village of] Mlada Gvardiya underwent professional disinfection in connection with the outbreak of anthrax.

The epidemiological investigation in connection with the 53-year-old's death continues. Meanwhile, it was announced on Sun [19 Jul 2015] that a 2nd possibly anthrax-infected animal had died in Mlada Gvardiya.

Dr Dochka Mihaylova, interim director of the Regional Health Inspectorate in Varna, announced that 22 out of the 26 individuals who had had contact with the anthrax-infected meat had tested negative for anthrax. The 22 people in question ate from the meat. Samples from the remaining 4 individuals are to be tested on Mon [20 Jul 2015]. Dr Mihaylova announced they had no complaints and continued taking the prescribed medicines.

Individuals who had contact with the 2nd dead animal will also be tested for anthrax.

--
